          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "From authors: As a result of the greater difficulty in",
                "observing the first excited-state deuteron group from",
                "the 6Li(t,d)7Li reaction, reliable data for this group",
                "could be obtained only in the angu1ai region between",
                "30. and 75.degr. (in the lab. system) at l.5MeV. This",
                "group also appears to exhibit a forward peak in the",
                "angular distribution similar to that of the ground-",
                "state group; however, the total cross-section for this",
                "group appears to be about a factor of 4 smaller than",
                "that of the ground-state group which is 190 mbn."
              ]
            }
          ],
